block content
  #message.alert.alert-success.hidden
  h2 Time required: 30 minutes
  p
    | Monitoring is all about how you can work systematically to maintain and improve your employees' performance. It's about having a good idea of ​​what they do and achieve in their work. Make it a habit to collect information about how your employees
    | perform their tasks. Below we present four different methods which you can learn to develop concrete examples of how you can monitor your employees. When you are done, you can print your own examples.
  .accordion
    h3
      span(title='Click for more information') Method 1: Remove sample from a person's work
    div
      p
        | This is one of the most effective methods to monitor anyone. This means observing something that the person has worked with.
      table#tbl0.tbl
        tr
          td Coworker
            p The person or persons in your group that you want to monitor
          td Sample
            p What the work you want to take a sample of
          td How monitor
            p How will you do this to take samples
        tr
          td
            i
              | Example:
              br
              |  Payroll Administrator
          td
            i
              | Example:
              br
              | Numbers that he registered in the payroll system
          td
            i
              | Example:
              br
              | Log on to the payroll system and look at some randomly selected individuals, and reports
